-- Usiminas Cut to `Neutral' at BTG Pactual on `Challenging' Local Outlook
-- Alexander Cuadros
-- 2010-07-30T11:56:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/usiminas-cut-to-neutral-at-btg-pactual-on-challenging-local-outlook.html

          
          
             Usinas Siderurgicas de Minas Gerais
SA , Brazil’s second-biggest steelmaker, was lowered to
“neutral” from “buy” at Banco BTG Pactual SA, which cited
its dependence on the domestic market.  
 Usiminas, as the company is known, faces a “challenging”
local outlook of lower volumes and higher costs, analysts  Edmo Chagas  and  Antonio Heluany  wrote in a note to clients today.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
